.TH "alloc_dma_buffer" 9 "alloc_dma_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_dma_buffer \- Create DMA Buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" alloc_dma_buffer
.BI "(struct vio_dev *vdev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma_handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vdev" 12
vio_dev struct
.IP "size" 12
Size field
.IP "dma_handle" 12
DMA address field
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates memory for the command queue and maps remote memory into an
ioba.

Returns a pointer to the buffer
